What you need to know:

The Bill, sponsored by leader of minority in the National Assembly John Mbadi (Suba South) sought to have former MPs who served between July 1, 1984 and January 1, 2001, get an enhanced monthly pension of at least Sh100,000.Currently, the MPs who served during the time take home from Sh2,000 to Sh8,000 while others get nothing despite serving the country.The Bill sailed through in the House on August 5, 2020 but theÂ President expressed his reservations on the advice of the Salaries and Remuneration Commission (SRC).